        <description>&lt;img src="https://blog.hangzhang.cv/leetcode.png" alt="Featured image of post Minimum Distance Between Three Equal Elements I" /&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;3740-minimum-distance-between-three-equal-elements-ihttpsleetcodecnproblemsminimum-distance-between-three-equal-elements-i&#34;&gt;&lt;a class=&#34;link&#34; href=&#34;https://leetcode.cn/problems/minimum-distance-between-three-equal-elements-i/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;
    &gt;3740. Minimum Distance Between Three Equal Elements I&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;algorithm-steps&#34;&gt;Algorithm Steps&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use &lt;code&gt;map&amp;lt;int, vector&amp;lt;int&amp;gt;&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; to record all the indices of each element&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;For each index array &lt;code&gt;p&lt;/code&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enumerate the length &lt;code&gt;&amp;gt;= 3&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Calculate &lt;code&gt;(p[i] - p[i-2]) * 2&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Take the minimum value&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&#34;complexity-analysis&#34;&gt;Complexity Analysis&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Time complexity: &lt;code&gt;O(n)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Space complexity: &lt;code&gt;O(n)&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
